.Dd March 31, 2004
.Dt NEWALIASES 1
.Os MASTODON
.Sh NAME
.Nm newaliases
.Nd rebuild the data base for the mail aliases file
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
@VHOST@.Op Ar host ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
rebuilds the random access data base for the mail aliases file
.Pa /etc/aliases .
@VHOST@When 
@VHOST@.Nm
@VHOST@is called with virtual host arguments, it will attempt to rebuild
@VHOST@the alias databases for those virtual hosts.
It must be run each time an alias file is modified in order
for the change to take effect.
.Sh FILES
.Pp
.Bl -tag -width @VPATH@/host/aliases -compact
.It Pa /etc/aliases
System aliases file.
@VHOST@.It Pa @VPATH@/host/aliases
@VHOST@The aliases file for the virtual host
@VHOST@.Ar host .
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr aliases 5 ,
.Xr postoffice 8
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
command appeared in
.Bx 4.0 .
